Understanding how network topologies differ between broadcast-oriented platforms and collaborative developer 
environments is crucial for optimizing information flow and identifying key contributors. This project analyzes 
the user-to-user connections within the Twitter Edge Nodes Dataset and the GitHub Social Network Graph. 
By comparing these networks, we aim to identify highly connected 'super-nodes' and determine whether 
a collaborative technical environment (GitHub) exhibits denser, more clustered communities compared to a 
general microblogging platform (Twitter).
